<emphasis box="[261,517,1953,1974]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="216">Scopulariopsis brevicaulis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(HKAS107658) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[684,702,1953,1974]" pageId="13" pageNumber="216">a.</emphasis>
Mature colony on PDA after 4 weeks with the sporulation. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1285,1304,1953,1974]" pageId="13" pageNumber="216">b.</emphasis>
Reverse of the colonies on PDA after 4 weeks. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[445,462,1989,2010]" pageId="13" pageNumber="216">c.</emphasis>
Sporulation of the colony with mycilium. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[871,891,1989,2010]" pageId="13" pageNumber="216">d.</emphasis>
Mature septate hyphae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1126,1143,1989,2010]" pageId="13" pageNumber="216">e.</emphasis>
Branched conidiophore bearing annellophores and conidia 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[393,427,2025,2047]" pageId="13" pageNumber="216">f–j.</emphasis>
Conidiogenous cells with developing conidia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[877,916,2025,2046]" pageId="13" pageNumber="216">k–r.</emphasis>
Conidia. Scale bars: d = 20 μm e, k, l = 10 μm, f–j, m–r = 5 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,158,941]" pageId="14" pageNumber="217">
